#: ../../G/GOSMACS.rst:9
msgid ""
"[contraction of ‘Gosling EMACS’] The first :ref:`EMACS`\\-in-C "
"implementation, predating but now largely eclipsed by :ref:`GNUMACS`\\. "
"Originally freeware; a commercial version was modestly popular as ‘UniPress "
"EMACS’ during the 1980s. The author, James Gosling, went on to invent "
":ref:`NeWS` and the programming language Java; the latter earned him "
":ref:`demigod` status."
msgstr ""
"[‘Gosling EMACS’の短縮形] 最初の\\ :ref:`EMACS`\\ のC言語実装。\\ :ref:`GNUMACS`\\ "
"より前に存在したが、今では大部分がそれに取って代わられた。元々はフリーウェアだった。1980年代には‘UniPress "
"EMACS’という商用版がそこそこ人気だった。作者のJames Goslingはその後\\ :ref:`NeWS`\\ "
"とプログラミング言語Javaを発明し、後者によって\\ :ref:`demigod`\\ の地位を得た。"
